HEADWORD: Obdiplostemonous
<hw>Ob*dip`lo*stem"o*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ob-</ets> + <ets>diplostemonous</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having twice as many stamens as petals, those of the outer set
being opposite the petals; -- said of flowers.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

